30:52.918 --> 30:55.018
Do you have...

30:56.888 --> 30:58.188
Asperger's?

30:58.190 --> 30:59.690
- What's wrong with you?

30:59.692 --> 31:01.892
- What?
It's just a curiosity.

31:01.894 --> 31:03.760
- You are barely
in my good graces.

31:03.762 --> 31:05.429
- There's no stigma.
A lot of perfectly--

31:05.431 --> 31:06.630
- just stop.

31:06.632 --> 31:08.398
Stop!

31:09.834 --> 31:12.035
- Very intelligent--
- stop!

31:17.842 --> 31:21.578
- Alright, so one mom
was a sociology professor

31:21.580 --> 31:24.114
the other worked
for the county.

31:24.116 --> 31:27.484
Very small town feel.

31:27.486 --> 31:32.122
Lots of big houses,
big yards, plenty of trees.

31:32.124 --> 31:35.726
Pretty classic sitcom setting
apart from the relative

31:35.728 --> 31:38.395
trailblazing on the
part of my parents.

31:38.397 --> 31:41.765
So one early spring weekday,

31:41.767 --> 31:43.233
and I remember
that it was a weekday

31:43.235 --> 31:44.935
because my parents weren't home,

31:44.937 --> 31:47.771
we went out
to the common area

31:47.773 --> 31:50.774
and there was this circular
grove of cherry trees,

31:50.776 --> 31:54.978
the grove had been planted
way back by the city fathers

31:54.980 --> 31:57.581
or whoever.

31:57.583 --> 32:01.852
And, so at this point
we had twelve, fifteen

32:01.854 --> 32:05.656
really beautiful
mature cherry trees.

32:05.658 --> 32:09.860
White pink flowers,
really stunning.

32:09.862 --> 32:12.262
You could see them for
miles and miles and miles.

32:12.264 --> 32:16.199
But today, this day,
they had transformed.

32:16.201 --> 32:21.305
And they were this nasty
green-black combination.

32:25.810 --> 32:28.545
And they were shimmering.

32:28.547 --> 32:30.814
Which is not exactly
the right word.

32:30.816 --> 32:33.984
Not like leaves
in the wind shimmering,

32:33.986 --> 32:38.455
but like the surface of water,
if the water was thick,

32:38.457 --> 32:41.725
like a sludge.

32:41.727 --> 32:43.860
I had obviously never done
drugs at that point in my life

32:43.862 --> 32:48.999
but it was...
It was like I was high.

32:49.001 --> 32:53.737
It was so wrong
and fundamentally unnatural.

32:53.739 --> 32:55.205
So we got closer,
you know,

32:55.207 --> 32:56.707
we want to see
what's going on,

32:56.709 --> 33:00.477
and we discover that
covering these trees,

33:00.479 --> 33:02.512
literally covering
every inch of these trees

33:02.514 --> 33:05.082
are these thousands
and thousands of

33:05.084 --> 33:09.553
green-black caterpillars.

33:09.555 --> 33:10.721
Every tree.

33:10.723 --> 33:11.922
And they were going to town.

33:11.924 --> 33:14.558
They were eating the leaves
and the stems

33:14.560 --> 33:16.426
and everything,
everything.

33:16.428 --> 33:17.928
And it was only the
cherry trees, I remember,

33:17.930 --> 33:20.097
for whatever reason
they weren't interested

33:20.099 --> 33:22.599
in any of the others.

33:22.601 --> 33:23.600
And...

33:23.602 --> 33:25.268
- Turn here.
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.

33:26.270 --> 33:30.240
And so we get up closer
and it's just this,

33:30.242 --> 33:36.346
like, gross and horrifying

33:36.348 --> 33:40.751
and amazing sight
and it's cool.

33:40.753 --> 33:42.352
But we knew that these trees
were a big deal

33:42.354 --> 33:44.388
so we went over to my
buddy Todd's house--

33:44.390 --> 33:46.690
- this is good,
let's stop here.

34:01.572 --> 34:03.874
- Do you want to get out?

34:04.242 --> 34:06.977
- No. Let's just sit here
for a while.

34:19.524 --> 34:21.458
So what happened?

34:21.460 --> 34:23.393
- Hmm?

34:25.329 --> 34:27.431
- D'you spray 'em?

34:27.433 --> 34:29.065
- Oh, uh, no.

34:29.068 --> 34:32.135
I guess there
wasn't time for that.

34:32.137 --> 34:33.670
We...
Todd's dad saw them,

34:33.672 --> 34:35.672
and he freaked out.

34:35.674 --> 34:38.641
Which was cool to see
an adult share your level

34:38.643 --> 34:40.476
of excitement about something.

34:40.478 --> 34:42.813
And he ran home

34:42.815 --> 34:45.482
and got on the landline
and called another dad.

34:45.484 --> 34:49.786
And the two of them
got out there with ladders

34:49.788 --> 34:54.024
and these big old
plastic buckets.

34:54.025 --> 34:57.994
And they got up there
and just started yanking

34:57.996 --> 35:00.430
fistfuls of caterpillars.

35:00.432 --> 35:05.936
They were tent caterpillars,
i found out later.

35:05.938 --> 35:07.871
And evidently,
every couple years

35:07.873 --> 35:11.174
there's just this
explosion of them.

35:11.176 --> 35:12.642
So we get these adults

35:12.644 --> 35:16.346
and they're throwing
caterpillars into the buckets.

35:16.348 --> 35:21.718
And we're eight so we're trying
to be as helpful as possible.

35:21.720 --> 35:26.056
And whenever these buckets
would get nearly full,

35:26.058 --> 35:27.958
we would take 'em down.

35:27.960 --> 35:31.128
And they were heavy.

35:31.130 --> 35:33.797
We'd take em down,
and there was a ditch nearby,

35:33.799 --> 35:37.000
and we'd pour em out into
the ditch and bring 'em back.

35:37.002 --> 35:42.539
And after probably
an hour or so of this

35:42.541 --> 35:44.875
we'd gotten most
of 'em off the trees,

35:44.877 --> 35:47.878
barring a couple dozen
stragglers or so.

35:47.880 --> 35:52.382
Meanwhile this ditch is
waist-high full of caterpillars.

35:52.384 --> 35:55.685
And one of the dads
went back to his house

35:55.687 --> 35:57.888
or his garage or something.

35:57.890 --> 36:02.759
And he had got a gas can
and brought it back.

36:02.761 --> 36:08.498
And they were just about to
start pouring it on this ditch.

36:08.500 --> 36:12.435
Um, and then I just...

36:12.437 --> 36:16.840
Like, I just ran out there

36:16.842 --> 36:18.341
and grabbed a bucket

36:18.343 --> 36:22.445
and started grabbing
caterpillars.

36:23.614 --> 36:25.582
- Why?

36:26.851 --> 36:28.118
- I don't' know.

36:28.120 --> 36:30.253
I didn't-- I certainly
didn't know at the time.

36:30.255 --> 36:34.291
I think that it was just,

36:34.293 --> 36:36.026
ya know,
i think was awful

36:36.028 --> 36:38.428
to see them about to get
destroyed like that.

36:38.430 --> 36:41.298
I think that was really awful.

36:41.300 --> 36:44.734
And I think I had the idea
that maybe I could save some.

36:44.736 --> 36:46.036
I didn't know what for.

36:46.038 --> 36:48.271
Later on,
i figured out something.

36:48.273 --> 36:53.944
But that initial impulse
is tough to explain.

36:53.946 --> 36:57.814
They let me keep, like, uh,
fifty or sixty of them

36:57.816 --> 36:59.382
and they...

36:59.384 --> 37:01.651
I had to promise to keep them
away from the trees.

37:01.653 --> 37:05.121
And, the adults,
they backed all of us kids up,

37:05.123 --> 37:06.056
way, way, way, back,

37:06.058 --> 37:08.291
and one of them
took the gas can

37:08.293 --> 37:09.926
and he poured gas
all over the ditch,

37:09.928 --> 37:14.898
and another one
flicked a match onto it.

37:14.900 --> 37:21.238
And... just this
enormous fireball.

37:21.240 --> 37:23.273
And, uh...

37:23.275 --> 37:25.175
- Let's get out.

38:05.983 --> 38:08.351
- Here we are again.

38:11.622 --> 38:13.056
- So what happened?

38:13.058 --> 38:15.191
- With what?

38:15.193 --> 38:17.027
- Uh, caterpillars.

38:17.029 --> 38:18.862
- Oh. Does this coming out
of my half-hour?

38:18.864 --> 38:20.630
- Keep it tight.
- Okay.

38:20.632 --> 38:23.066
- Uh, where was I?

38:23.501 --> 38:25.702
- Uh... fireball.

38:25.704 --> 38:27.537
- Yeah, right!
- Pocket full of caterpillars.

38:27.539 --> 38:30.240
- Yes, yes, yes, yes.
So, um...

38:30.242 --> 38:32.542
Have you ever heard
the bill cosby routine

38:32.544 --> 38:36.212
about saving a snowball
for the summer?

38:36.214 --> 38:37.714
Oh man. Okay.

38:37.716 --> 38:40.650
It's good.
You should check it out.

38:40.652 --> 38:43.920
Anyway, so, uh,

38:43.922 --> 38:46.690
I've got these, like,
fifty, sixty caterpillars

38:46.692 --> 38:50.160
and I figure
I'll take 'em home,

38:50.162 --> 38:52.095
they turn into cocoon's
and you know,

38:52.097 --> 38:53.563
in my little science brain,

38:53.565 --> 38:55.699
then I'd have butterflies,
right?

38:55.701 --> 38:59.402
A whole basket of butterflies
to surprise my moms with.

38:59.404 --> 39:02.739
I thought it would be
a very, very sweet gesture.

39:02.741 --> 39:06.242
They ended up separating
when I was in college.

39:06.244 --> 39:10.380
And then my mom Cindy
passed away last year.

39:10.382 --> 39:11.681
Which I'm sure you...

39:11.683 --> 39:13.249
- Yeah, sorry.

39:13.251 --> 39:14.551
- Thank you for saying that.

39:14.553 --> 39:16.419
It is what it is.

39:16.421 --> 39:19.956
So, so Patrick's dad
gives me this coffee can

39:19.958 --> 39:22.759
and I put 'em in there,
and I take 'em home,

39:22.761 --> 39:24.260
and I put 'em in the basement

39:24.262 --> 39:27.297
where I know nobody but me
is ever going to look for them.

39:27.299 --> 39:33.770
And then I every day just keep
bringing 'em leaves and water,

39:33.772 --> 39:35.739
and I wait.

39:35.741 --> 39:39.976
But I notice something
kind of weird is happening.

39:39.978 --> 39:41.444
I started, ya know,
with like,

39:41.446 --> 39:44.047
fifty or sixty caterpillars,
at least

39:44.049 --> 39:47.817
and now at this point,
maybe I've got thirty tops.

39:47.819 --> 39:50.954
So, I can them out
of the coffee tin,

39:50.956 --> 39:53.556
I picked out
a couple dead ones,

39:53.558 --> 39:56.960
but it didn't make sense,
the math didn't add up.

39:56.962 --> 39:58.628
And then a couple days later

39:58.630 --> 40:01.131
I figured out
what was going on.

40:01.133 --> 40:03.900
Ya know,
start with fifty,

40:04.335 --> 40:11.408
thirty, twenty, ten,
and then finally three.

40:12.843 --> 40:18.581
Three enormous,
disgusting caterpillars

40:18.583 --> 40:20.483
with the remains
of all of their brothers

40:20.485 --> 40:22.952
and sisters inside of them.

40:22.954 --> 40:25.989
You can imagine the
feelings that I had as a kid.

40:25.991 --> 40:30.660
This was supposed to be this
really sweet thing for my moms,

40:30.662 --> 40:34.631
and it had become
a nightmare.

40:34.633 --> 40:36.833
I took 'em out
onto the concrete,

40:36.835 --> 40:39.502
grabbed a big hammer,

40:39.504 --> 40:44.774
and I smashed down
as hard as I fucking could.

40:53.417 --> 40:56.219
I never told anybody that story.

41:02.660 --> 41:03.860
What?

41:06.898 --> 41:08.731
- What?

41:14.505 --> 41:16.206
- Why would you
tell me that story?

41:16.208 --> 41:19.342
- I don't know.
I don't know.

41:19.344 --> 41:21.377
I wanted to tell a story.

41:21.379 --> 41:23.480
I don't like silence,
i just started talking.

41:23.482 --> 41:25.081
It came-- I don't--

41:25.083 --> 41:27.917
- jeez, Louise.
- Okay. Okay...

41:33.290 --> 41:35.859
What?!

41:35.861 --> 41:37.760
- It's just, it's, uh...

41:40.498 --> 41:44.033
- I assume there's some
kind of encryption key.

41:44.035 --> 41:48.004
- In 2010 and 2011,
you lived with a woman, right?

41:48.006 --> 41:49.706
- Yeah.

41:49.708 --> 41:51.207
- Your current
license plate number

41:51.209 --> 41:54.544
and her mother's maiden name,
interchanged.

41:54.546 --> 41:56.746
But everything reversed.

41:56.748 --> 42:00.583
So, last digit of
the license plate first,

42:00.585 --> 42:03.353
then last of the name.

42:03.355 --> 42:05.255
Then it alternates.
Make sense?

42:05.257 --> 42:10.260
- Five, a, nine, I.

42:10.262 --> 42:12.262
Blah, blah, blah, blah, blah.
Like that, right?

42:12.264 --> 42:14.197
- First letter
of the last name cap,

42:14.199 --> 42:16.032
the rest lowercase.

42:16.034 --> 42:18.601
License plate number all caps.

42:18.603 --> 42:19.702
- Okay.

42:19.704 --> 42:21.905
So these files contain
what exactly?

42:21.907 --> 42:23.306
- About two-thousand names.

42:23.308 --> 42:26.776
Their last known location,
previous address,

42:26.778 --> 42:28.978
profession sometimes,
social security number,

42:28.980 --> 42:31.214
phone, email, ip.

42:31.216 --> 42:32.982
- And what is important
about them?

42:32.984 --> 42:35.285
- You're going to
have to find out.

42:36.654 --> 42:38.888
- What prompted
this change of heart?

42:38.890 --> 42:40.790
Is it what this list is,
or represents?

42:40.792 --> 42:42.592
Something in the news--

42:42.594 --> 42:45.628
- what do you mean,
change of heart?

42:45.630 --> 42:48.131
- A shift of values.

42:48.133 --> 42:51.834
I mean, it sounds like
something of an awakening, no?

42:51.836 --> 42:53.436
- No.

42:54.572 --> 42:55.738
- No?

42:55.740 --> 42:58.641
- No, I haven't had
a change of heart.

42:58.643 --> 43:00.643
- Then why are you doing this?

43:00.645 --> 43:03.580
- Because I hold what I do
to a high standard.

43:03.582 --> 43:06.849
I think cleaning ourselves
of what's on that drive

43:06.851 --> 43:09.319
makes us better,
stronger.

43:09.321 --> 43:12.622
- And you don't conflate
whatever these abuses are

43:12.624 --> 43:15.124
to the core of what you do?

43:15.126 --> 43:17.660
- You don't think what I do
is very valuable, do you?

43:17.662 --> 43:19.262
- I think that we
shouldn't get into it.
- No.

43:19.264 --> 43:20.496
- Let's stick to facts.

43:20.498 --> 43:22.665
- No, no.
Let's get into it.

43:22.667 --> 43:25.301
Here, let's start with this.

43:25.303 --> 43:30.006
This, this device that you
think affords you privacy,

43:30.008 --> 43:31.941
did you make this?

43:31.943 --> 43:32.942
- I get it.

43:32.944 --> 43:34.844
- Do you?

43:34.846 --> 43:36.980
This incredibly complex device

43:36.982 --> 43:39.649
with thousands
of precise components

43:39.651 --> 43:41.818
assembled by people
whose lives are shit

43:41.820 --> 43:42.986
working for you.

43:42.988 --> 43:44.120
Are you under the impression

43:44.122 --> 43:46.356
that you are just
some fortunate guy.

43:46.358 --> 43:50.126
And the rest of the world wants
to work with poor eyesight

43:50.128 --> 43:51.661
and hungry stomachs
and bloody fingers

43:51.663 --> 43:53.896
for you to amuse yourself?

43:53.898 --> 43:56.232
These things do not just happen.

43:56.234 --> 44:00.303
People wield power
to make them happen.

44:00.305 --> 44:03.172
If you honestly think
you could enjoy

44:03.174 --> 44:05.074
anything close
to your lifestyle:

44:05.076 --> 44:08.144
Your iPads
and your fair trade coffee

44:08.146 --> 44:11.214
and your discount airfares,
and your press freedoms,

44:11.216 --> 44:15.852
without the threat of
enormous power behind you,

44:15.854 --> 44:17.887
you're delusional.

44:17.889 --> 44:19.722
You are a party
to these actions,

44:19.724 --> 44:23.092
you are complicit,
and deep down you know it.

44:24.995 --> 44:27.864
I do what I do
because someone has to.

44:27.866 --> 44:30.900
This world is chaos
and fear

44:30.902 --> 44:32.402
and desperation
and violence,

44:32.404 --> 44:35.104
and the only thing that has
ever brought any security

44:35.106 --> 44:36.506
and order to it

44:36.508 --> 44:40.243
is the careful and ruthless
application of power.

44:56.226 --> 44:58.361
Get in the car.

45:07.671 --> 45:10.273
Go, go, go, go , go!

45:11.975 --> 45:13.710
Okay, go.

45:31.228 --> 45:33.396
- Are they FBI?

45:33.398 --> 45:35.331
- No.

45:40.037 --> 45:42.138
- Oh shit.

45:53.584 --> 45:54.951
Fuck.

45:54.953 --> 45:57.286
Shit, shit.

46:12.469 --> 46:13.603
So if they're not cops,

46:13.605 --> 46:15.772
they clearly have
my license plate.

46:17.474 --> 46:19.275
They gonna figure out
who I am?

46:19.277 --> 46:22.111
Are they going to come
harass me back home?

46:24.314 --> 46:26.449
- Are they?
- I don't know.

46:26.451 --> 46:28.017
- You think if I thought
any of this would've happened

46:28.019 --> 46:30.520
I would have come out here?

46:30.522 --> 46:33.356
- You know what,
i have not done anything wrong.

46:33.358 --> 46:34.791
Have I?

46:34.793 --> 46:36.058
What have I done?
I met you, we talked.

46:36.060 --> 46:38.961
I told you a story
about fucking caterpillars.

46:38.963 --> 46:40.797
Huh, right?

46:44.168 --> 46:47.069
- I need you to throw the
USB drive out the window.

46:48.672 --> 46:50.640
- Okay, hang on.

46:51.074 --> 46:52.842
- What do you think
is going on here?

46:52.844 --> 46:56.045
Do you think these are just
some rednecks fucking with us?

46:56.047 --> 46:57.814
You asked
if we broke any laws,

46:57.816 --> 46:58.981
the better question is whether

46:58.983 --> 47:01.217
there's anything of value
inside this car.

47:01.219 --> 47:02.585
There are two things.

47:02.587 --> 47:05.421
What's on that drive
and what's in my head.

47:05.423 --> 47:08.891
You are only in possession
of one of them.

47:08.893 --> 47:09.826
- Yeah.

47:10.828 --> 47:12.228
Yeah, okay.

47:14.298 --> 47:17.033
- Wait until there's a turn.
I don't want them to see it.

47:43.460 --> 47:46.395
When I tell you I want you
to throw it as hard as you can

47:46.397 --> 47:48.064
away from the road.

47:48.832 --> 47:50.199
You ready?

48:08.552 --> 48:09.585
Now!

48:20.965 --> 48:22.331
Thank you.

48:22.333 --> 48:24.400
- Well, it is what it is.

48:40.417 --> 48:42.752
- How does this thing
do off road?

48:42.754 --> 48:45.521
- I live in Chicago.
I don't know.

48:45.722 --> 48:48.257
- If we get the chance
i might need to drive.

48:48.525 --> 48:50.192
- Okay.

48:58.769 --> 49:00.503
- Shit.

49:00.505 --> 49:02.338
We need a bridge.

49:04.908 --> 49:07.176
Does it narrow?
Does it get any narrower?

49:07.178 --> 49:09.278
- I do not know what you're
trying to ask me right now.

49:09.280 --> 49:11.514
- Never mind,
just keep it steady.

49:11.516 --> 49:14.350
- I don't know what you
think I've been doing up here.

49:15.619 --> 49:17.954
- Does this back window open?

49:18.722 --> 49:20.790
- No.
What are you doing?

49:25.062 --> 49:27.797
- Is there anything identifying
you in this bag?

49:27.799 --> 49:29.665
- Uh, yeah, my stuff.

49:29.667 --> 49:32.702
- Anything sewn into the lining.
Anything like that?

49:32.704 --> 49:34.236
- I don't know.

49:34.238 --> 49:36.806
What are you--
what are you gonna do?

49:42.446 --> 49:44.413
Whoa, whoa, what the fuck!

49:44.415 --> 49:46.983
- They'll stop for it.
Keep driving.

49:51.922 --> 49:53.489
Speed up!

49:54.758 --> 49:57.727
And watch for the next car
you see coming towards us.

50:00.664 --> 50:02.598
As soon as you see it I want
you to pull into their Lane

50:02.600 --> 50:04.166
and stop immediately.

50:04.168 --> 50:06.402
- You want me to run
head first into another car?

50:06.404 --> 50:09.271
I want you to block their Lane.

50:09.273 --> 50:12.408
- If I can.
I'm not going to hit anybody.

50:33.630 --> 50:35.898
Alright, I think I see one.

50:35.900 --> 50:38.134
- Pull into their Lane.

50:43.473 --> 50:44.707
- Shit.

50:44.709 --> 50:46.742
Jesus Christ...

50:51.815 --> 50:53.582
- Come forward please!

50:53.584 --> 50:54.784
Let's go!

50:54.786 --> 50:57.053
Keep it to this side.
Let's go, let's go!

50:59.156 --> 51:00.089
